01:42:28,700 --> 01:42:31,050
我們從來沒有慶祝你的生日。

938
01:42:44,530 --> 01:42:46,030
這不是很棒嗎？

939
01:42:48,310 --> 01:42:50,570
畢竟這一次，它並沒有破壞。

940
01:43:07,150 --> 01:43:08,910
我會在裡面等他們回來。

941
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:47,780
We have come very far, enduring many hardships.

942
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:53,300
But at last, we found a place where we can be safe.

943
00:01:53,950 --> 00:01:55,120
Together.

944
00:01:55,570 --> 00:01:57,650
At the other end of the ocean.

945
00:02:13,620 --> 00:02:15,700
It's not how I remember it.

946
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:19,300
Mum had put all her hopes

947
00:02:19,340 --> 00:02:21,680
on the house where she had grown up.

948
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:24,080
It had been waiting for us,

949
00:02:24,540 --> 00:02:27,550
frozen in time for over thirty years.

950
00:02:40,750 --> 00:02:42,540
Is someone there?

951
00:02:46,060 --> 00:02:48,300
Just a coat stand in the mirror, Sam.

952
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:50,320
Don't be afraid.

953
00:03:01,340 --> 00:03:03,760
It's not a step to take lightly.

954
00:03:05,630 --> 00:03:07,460
We're no longer Fairbairns.

955
00:03:08,350 --> 00:03:12,050
From now on, our last name will be "Marrowbone".

956
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,600
Just like this house,

957
00:03:13,750 --> 00:03:15,650
which will be our new home.

958
00:03:20,090 --> 00:03:23,180
Once you cross that line, there'll be no memories.

959
00:03:23,670 --> 00:03:26,980
Our story begins here.

960
00:03:27,540 --> 00:03:29,350
Will he ever find us, Mummy?

961
00:03:30,640 --> 00:03:31,810
Who?

962
00:03:34,070 --> 00:03:35,990
You see, I've crossed the line.

963
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:37,870
I must've forgotten already.

964
00:03:38,550 --> 00:03:40,890
No one will bother us again.

965
00:03:41,580 --> 00:03:42,750
Ever.

966
00:04:12,820 --> 00:04:15,570
We wanted to believe that we would be safe.

967
00:04:16,570 --> 00:04:19,240
That we too had a chance of happiness.

968
00:04:20,420 --> 00:04:24,510
That Mum's illness had disappeared with the rest of our problems.

969
00:04:24,730 --> 00:04:26,920
The darkness we'd left behind seem to vanish

970
00:04:27,060 --> 00:04:29,160
in the light of those summer days.

971
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:32,380
Nobody knew us.

972
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:35,470
We could be free for the first time.

973
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:40,310
And we were about to make a new friend

974
00:04:40,410 --> 00:04:42,740
that would change our lives forever.

975
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:44,450
Oh, look at that, Sam!

976
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:47,500
This must be the place they call "The Red Witch Rock".

977
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:48,840
It's a skull.

978
00:04:48,950 --> 00:04:51,280
Let's go back, Billy. I don't like it.

979
00:04:52,130 --> 00:04:53,520
Who goes there?

980
00:04:53,660 --> 00:04:56,220
How dare you invade my dwellings.

981
00:04:57,520 --> 00:04:59,130
I'm Sam Marrowbone.

982
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:01,790
These are my two brothers, Billy and Jack.

983
00:05:01,870 --> 00:05:03,910
And this is my sister Jane.

984
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:06,790
You have entered the Red Witch lands.

985
00:05:07,380 --> 00:05:09,380
See that passage to your right?

986
00:05:09,730 --> 00:05:11,480
You must cross it.

987
00:05:11,970 --> 00:05:14,520
If you mean well, you'd be free to go.

988
00:05:14,890 --> 00:05:17,230
But if you hide evil within your heart,

989
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:20,540
the walls would close in and trap you forever.

990
00:05:21,110 --> 00:05:22,530
Do you dare cross it?

991
00:05:22,610 --> 00:05:23,470
Jack, no.

992
00:05:23,530 --> 00:05:25,000
-Come on! -Come on, Sammy!

993
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:26,570
Be brave.

994
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:31,740
The walls are closing in, we shouldn't be here.

995
00:05:31,850 --> 00:05:33,850
Your soul must have been good.

996
00:05:34,730 --> 00:05:36,220
It's very slippy here.

997
00:05:38,490 --> 00:05:40,350
Hello, little one.

998
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:43,540
Come closer.

999
00:05:46,350 --> 00:05:47,750
My name is Allie.

1000
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:50,240
Are you a prisoner of the Red Witch?

1001
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:51,590
Yes.

1002
00:05:52,130 --> 00:05:54,710
She punished me for breaking into her garden.

1003
00:05:54,780 --> 00:05:56,930
Leaving me trapped until someone

1004
00:05:57,020 --> 00:06:00,050
dared cross the passageway and rescue me.

1005
00:06:00,420 --> 00:06:02,040
Now, is that someone you?

1006
00:06:03,420 --> 00:06:07,190
Take these acorns in return.

1007
00:06:07,460 --> 00:06:09,280
They aren't much now, but

1008
00:06:09,470 --> 00:06:12,190
they'll grow big and strong with our friendship.

1009
00:06:13,340 --> 00:06:14,820
They're magic.

1010
00:06:20,810 --> 00:06:22,430
So now that you're free,

1011
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:25,290
where would you like to go?

1012
00:06:49,420 --> 00:06:52,150
At the end of that unforgettable day,

1013
00:06:52,210 --> 00:06:54,340
Allie was already one of us.

1014
00:06:54,450 --> 00:06:56,450
Stop. Wait, okay, move forward.

1015
00:06:56,780 --> 00:06:57,780
Why?

1016
00:06:57,820 --> 00:06:59,460
It's too beautiful. Can I...?

1017
00:06:59,910 --> 00:07:01,760
Get close together, come on.

1018
00:07:02,410 --> 00:07:04,040
You guys ready?

1019
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:06,380
One, two...

1020
00:07:06,820 --> 00:07:08,040
Great.

1021
00:07:09,690 --> 00:07:10,930
Perfect.

1022
00:07:12,340 --> 00:07:13,850
We began again.

1023
00:07:14,530 --> 00:07:16,210
We forgot the past.

1024
00:07:18,340 --> 00:07:20,420
And we started a new life.

1025
00:07:21,810 --> 00:07:24,810
For a while, we all bought in to that illusion.

1026
00:07:26,850 --> 00:07:29,410
But the journey to America had taken what little strength

1027
00:07:29,440 --> 00:07:31,070
Mum had left in her.

1028
00:07:31,250 --> 00:07:33,070
Little did we know,

1029
00:07:33,180 --> 00:07:35,700
that would be our last summer together.

1030
00:07:44,300 --> 00:07:46,090
Bury me in the garden.

1031
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:49,000
I showed you where.

1032
00:07:49,870 --> 00:07:53,590
You just have to turn 21.

1033
00:07:53,910 --> 00:07:57,340
Stay hidden until then

1034
00:07:58,840 --> 00:08:01,500
and no law will take them from you.

1035
00:08:03,380 --> 00:08:05,130
Swear to me.

1036
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:08,490
You'll stay together.

1037
00:08:12,350 --> 00:08:14,150
Always stay together.

1038
00:08:15,850 --> 00:08:17,270
I swear.

1039
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:23,320
Have a safe place ready.

1040
00:08:24,850 --> 00:08:27,270
In case he finds you.

1041
00:08:31,420 --> 00:08:33,170
In the cupboard.

1042
00:08:33,560 --> 00:08:35,140
On the left.

1043
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:01,490
You lied.

1044
00:09:02,780 --> 00:09:04,460
You lied in court.

1045
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:08,190
You kept his money all this time.

1046
00:09:14,750 --> 00:09:16,300
"My dearest Jack,

1047
00:09:16,530 --> 00:09:19,800
"I'm so sorry I won't be there for you as you grow up.

1048
00:09:20,540 --> 00:09:22,670
"I no longer have the strength.

1049
00:09:23,230 --> 00:09:27,290
"Jane will be Sam's mother, as it was meant to be.

1050
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:31,160
"Tell Billy to not let his anger

1051
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:33,230
"take his beautiful heart.

1052
00:09:34,790 --> 00:09:37,120
"And you, my Jack, when the time comes,

1053
00:09:37,210 --> 00:09:39,770
"do not forget to open your heart to love.

1054
00:09:41,430 --> 00:09:43,300
"You must keep them safe.

1055
00:09:44,510 --> 00:09:45,800
"Always.

1056
00:09:46,980 --> 00:09:51,270
Your loving mother, Rose Marrowbone".

1057
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,700
Nothing,

1058
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:04,920
no one,

1059
00:10:05,330 --> 00:10:06,330
ever...

1060
00:10:06,810 --> 00:10:08,560
will separate us.

1061
00:10:10,730 --> 00:10:12,230
We are one.

1062
00:10:16,350 --> 00:10:17,820
Repeat after me.

1063
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:21,050
Nothing.

1064
00:10:23,730 --> 00:10:25,070
Nothing.

1065
00:10:25,770 --> 00:10:27,100
No one.

1066
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,020
-No one. -No one.

1067
00:10:30,520 --> 00:10:31,770
Ever.

1068
00:10:33,220 --> 00:10:34,810
-Ever. -Ever.

1069
00:10:36,540 --> 00:10:37,720
Ever.

1070
00:10:39,630 --> 00:10:41,040
We are one.

1071
00:10:41,660 --> 00:10:43,420
-We are one. -We are one.

1072
00:10:47,160 --> 00:10:49,170
We sealed our promise.

1073
00:10:49,560 --> 00:10:52,050
And we started hiding from the world...

1074
00:10:52,530 --> 00:10:54,730
until I turned 21.

1075
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:36,690
Jack!

1076
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:42,480
Jack! Jack!

1077
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:56,990
Six months later

1078
00:12:28,290 --> 00:12:31,070
I'm tired of being locked up in this house.

1079
00:12:32,490 --> 00:12:34,560
It won't be long before your birthday, Jack.

1080
00:12:34,660 --> 00:12:37,090
We should start thinking about your party.

1081
00:12:40,480 --> 00:12:43,220
That lawyer Porter was hanging on the fence last week again.

1082
00:12:43,380 --> 00:12:45,230
We'll be done with him soon enough.

1083
00:12:45,260 --> 00:12:47,650
Come Christmas time it will all be different.

1084
00:12:47,830 --> 00:12:49,010
You'll see, Billy.

1085
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,420
Billy! Billy!

1086
00:12:51,420 --> 00:12:52,140
What Sam?

1087
00:12:52,220 --> 00:12:53,590
I heard a noise behind the mirror

1088
00:12:53,620 --> 00:12:55,100
and the cover is falling off.

1089
00:12:55,180 --> 00:12:56,330
If you don't do something,

1090
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:58,060
ghost might be able to see us again.

1091
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,430
Stop being such a baby.

1092
00:12:59,550 --> 00:13:01,490
You don't need to be scared.

1093
00:13:02,220 --> 00:13:04,630
Sam, the ghost has been gone for months.

1094
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:08,280
Here, give me this.

1095
00:13:09,990 --> 00:13:11,330
Scoundrel?

1096
00:13:15,170 --> 00:13:17,640
Come on, Scoundrel, come get your breakfast.

1097
00:13:18,100 --> 00:13:20,600
So that's what's making the noises behind the walls.

1098
00:13:20,710 --> 00:13:22,160
It's that big rat.

1099
00:13:22,830 --> 00:13:25,010
Sam, stop feeding it.

1100
00:13:25,180 --> 00:13:27,260
It's making holes all over the house.

1101
00:13:27,430 --> 00:13:28,870
Do you want me to let her starve?

1102
00:13:28,940 --> 00:13:30,200
You don't know where that thing has been.

1103
00:13:30,220 --> 00:13:31,590
All right? You could get rabies.

1104
00:13:31,650 --> 00:13:33,670
She won't bite me, she's my friend.

1105
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:35,570
Terrible thing, rabies.

1106
00:13:35,710 --> 00:13:37,020
You'll get foam coming out your mouth

1107
00:13:37,040 --> 00:13:38,520
until your insides are all rotten.

1108
00:13:38,580 --> 00:13:40,100
I'll have to spend my last bullet on you.

1109
00:13:40,170 --> 00:13:42,560
Then I'll hide behind the mirror and scream and cry all night

1110
00:13:42,610 --> 00:13:44,210
and you'll never sleep again.

1111
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:46,330
Yeah, but the dead don't cry or scream.

1112
00:13:46,520 --> 00:13:49,950
Tell me that next time you hear the ghost in the middle of the night.

1113
00:14:46,860 --> 00:14:48,010
Oh, fuck.

1114
00:14:48,880 --> 00:14:49,880
Ah!

1115
00:14:57,520 --> 00:14:58,640
Jack!

1116
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:05,090
No extra money, no nonsense.

1117
00:15:05,560 --> 00:15:06,810
We'll see.

1118
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:10,320
Hello.

1119
00:15:10,380 --> 00:15:13,720
We'll follow you on the map, Jack, so you don't feel alone.

1120
00:15:24,170 --> 00:15:26,350
He's just left the Marrowbone home.

1121
00:15:26,440 --> 00:15:28,490
He's going through the forest.

1122
00:15:32,050 --> 00:15:33,580
That was a bird.

1123
00:15:33,890 --> 00:15:37,760
And then he goes down the tunnel.

1124
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:39,620
Through the tunnel.

1125
00:15:41,700 --> 00:15:45,400
And then, he goes out of the tunnel...

1126
00:15:45,860 --> 00:15:48,930
and goes on the bridge...

1127
00:15:51,220 --> 00:15:52,760
and then...

1128
00:15:54,170 --> 00:15:56,890
Oh, he should see Allie's farm by now.

1129
00:15:56,980 --> 00:15:59,190
-Say, "Hi, Allie"! -Hi, Allie.

1130
00:15:59,270 --> 00:16:03,170
-Hi, we miss you! -We miss you.

1131
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:09,560
And he goes through the bumpy mud.

1132
00:16:09,810 --> 00:16:12,320
And he goes through the path.

1133
00:16:12,870 --> 00:16:14,960
He goes all the way up.

1134
00:16:17,180 --> 00:16:20,720
-And now he's getting near town. -Oh.

1135
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:26,410
He's almost there.

1136
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:31,970
And then he goes into that shop.

1137
00:16:32,580 --> 00:16:34,950
Careful, Jack.

1138
00:16:35,700 --> 00:16:37,540
Be brave, Jack.

1139
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:40,660
Catch me if you can!

1140
00:16:40,830 --> 00:16:42,700
Two weeks ago today...

1141
00:16:45,960 --> 00:16:47,340
Oh, Jack.

1142
00:16:47,430 --> 00:16:49,950
I was beginning to think you wouldn't show up this week.

1143
00:16:50,310 --> 00:16:52,110
Hm, they smell delicious.

1144
00:16:53,560 --> 00:16:54,980
You bring a list?

1145
00:16:58,590 --> 00:17:00,560
Thousands saluted the American flag

1146
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:02,380
stiff with wires so that it would wave.

1147
00:17:02,480 --> 00:17:04,640
Then inspected the conditions of the lunar module...

1148
00:17:04,880 --> 00:17:07,650
How's your mother feeling? Any better?

1149
00:17:08,650 --> 00:17:10,290
Not really.

1150
00:17:10,550 --> 00:17:12,250
It's this change in weather.

1151
00:17:12,320 --> 00:17:13,810
I'm sorry to hear that.

1152
00:17:13,930 --> 00:17:15,760
I'm sure she'll get well soon, though.

1153
00:17:15,900 --> 00:17:17,530
Give her my love, will you?

1154
00:18:21,420 --> 00:18:23,360
What's with all of these books?

1155
00:18:24,070 --> 00:18:25,690
They came in on Friday.

1156
00:18:26,030 --> 00:18:30,120
From a library weeding in a place I used to work in Portland.

1157
00:18:30,550 --> 00:18:34,460
I say we let their weeds become our flowers.

1158
00:18:55,710 --> 00:18:57,310
I've missed you.

1159
00:18:58,470 --> 00:19:00,670
I'm sorry I didn't make it last week.

1160
00:19:01,520 --> 00:19:02,850
It's okay.

1161
00:19:03,590 --> 00:19:05,840
Oh, I have the book that you asked for.

1162
00:19:11,310 --> 00:19:12,310
Thank you.

1163
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:14,070
You're welcome.

1164
00:19:14,180 --> 00:19:17,080
Uh, how's Sam coming along? Does he need another one?

1165
00:19:19,550 --> 00:19:21,700
How can he read so fast?

1166
00:19:21,820 --> 00:19:24,550
It's almost at least 300 pages long.

1167
00:19:26,230 --> 00:19:28,070
I miss the little guy.

1168
00:19:28,810 --> 00:19:30,810
And Jane, and Billy.

1169
00:19:31,540 --> 00:19:34,130
It's so easy for me to just pop by, I could...

1170
00:19:34,210 --> 00:19:35,820
Perhaps my mother's better.

1171
00:19:39,650 --> 00:19:40,910
Hello there.

1172
00:19:41,560 --> 00:19:43,150
Mr. Porter.

1173
00:19:46,860 --> 00:19:48,020
So?

1174
00:19:49,100 --> 00:19:50,470
What do you think?

1175
00:19:50,540 --> 00:19:52,160
Very smart.

1176
00:19:52,310 --> 00:19:54,960
Do you remember that position I told you about in New York?

1177
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:56,870
Parker & Jameson.

1178
00:19:59,890 --> 00:20:02,220
Does this mean...?

1179
00:20:02,370 --> 00:20:05,450
Well, it means that they fell under my charm and I got the job.

1180
00:20:05,640 --> 00:20:09,330
It is wonderful, Tom. I'm just so happy for you.

1181
00:20:09,460 --> 00:20:14,550
Anyway, I happen to stroll past the strand and...

1182
00:20:14,730 --> 00:20:18,480
I couldn't help thinking of...

1183
00:20:19,180 --> 00:20:20,320
you.

1184
00:20:20,560 --> 00:20:21,900
What is that?

1185
00:20:22,080 --> 00:20:25,080
It's a donation, if you will, for the library.

1186
00:20:32,980 --> 00:20:35,570
This is a first edition, I can't possibly accept this.

1187
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:37,460
I just wish you could've seen the place.

1188
00:20:37,560 --> 00:20:40,700
You would love it. Maybe I should take you sometime.

1189
00:20:40,820 --> 00:20:42,530
You ever been to New York City?

1190
00:21:05,970 --> 00:21:07,510
Jack Fairbairn.

1191
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:10,440
It's Marrowbone now.

1192
00:21:11,350 --> 00:21:13,420
We go by my mother's last name.

1193
00:21:14,150 --> 00:21:15,730
Right, well, uh...

1194
00:21:16,180 --> 00:21:18,590
speaking of which, the other heirs have already signed off.

1195
00:21:18,750 --> 00:21:21,440
And I need to collect the transfer charges on the estate.

1196
00:21:22,320 --> 00:21:23,950
I'll come around the house tomorrow.

1197
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:26,530
Tell your mother have a bank check ready for 200 dollars.

1198
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:29,530
She's quite unwell.

1199
00:21:30,390 --> 00:21:32,490
Perhaps it would be best if I took the papers and

1200
00:21:32,620 --> 00:21:35,090
I have my mother sign them and bring them back to you.

1201
00:21:35,420 --> 00:21:37,300
I need to certify the signatures.

1202
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:41,350
I'll be there tomorrow. Noon.

1203
00:21:54,090 --> 00:21:55,260
Bye, Jack.

1204
00:21:55,790 --> 00:21:57,060
I'll see you soon.

1205
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,470
Fucking lawyers.

