Why can't I live with the girl that I love?

1477
00:48:07,960 --> 00:48:09,510
What about our promise?

1478
00:48:09,890 --> 00:48:11,750
Does that mean nothing to you anymore?

1479
00:48:11,920 --> 00:48:14,210
The things that I do to keep you all safe.

1480
00:48:14,550 --> 00:48:15,710
Safe?

1481
00:48:15,880 --> 00:48:17,890
Oh, tell me, what about this feels safe?

1482
00:48:17,960 --> 00:48:20,580
We're trapped in here while you go around doing whatever you please.

1483
00:48:20,630 --> 00:48:22,210
But that's just fine, Jack.

1484
00:48:22,250 --> 00:48:23,320
-Be quiet. -Fine.

1485
00:48:23,410 --> 00:48:24,550
-Maybe she should come -Be quiet.

1486
00:48:24,600 --> 00:48:25,600
and live her then, huh?

1487
00:48:25,670 --> 00:48:26,870
Why? Why be quiet?

1488
00:48:26,940 --> 00:48:28,260
-Shut up. -Tell her about Mum.

1489
00:48:28,350 --> 00:48:29,610
-Billy! -Tell her the truth about Dad.

1490
00:48:29,680 --> 00:48:30,850
-Why can't you handle it? -Get out!

1491
00:48:30,900 --> 00:48:31,650
'Cause you know it's the truth.

1492
00:48:31,730 --> 00:48:33,040
-Why don't you tell her the truth? -Get out!

1493
00:48:33,070 --> 00:48:35,130
-Billy! -Jane, don't touch me!

1494
00:48:35,230 --> 00:48:36,520
Don't shut the door on me!

1495
00:48:36,690 --> 00:48:37,860
-Get out! -Why?

1496
00:48:37,970 --> 00:48:40,210
-Get out! Get out! -Why, because you want me to leave?

1497
00:48:40,280 --> 00:48:41,560
-You want me to leave? -Leave me--

1498
00:48:41,580 --> 00:48:43,110
You need me more than I need you!

1499
00:48:43,170 --> 00:48:44,030
Leave!

1500
00:49:29,200 --> 00:49:31,120
Are you feeling better?

1501
00:49:32,100 --> 00:49:33,670
Shhh.

1502
00:49:36,540 --> 00:49:38,360
My head has exploded.

1503
00:49:42,630 --> 00:49:44,630
Take it easy on him.

1504
00:49:45,540 --> 00:49:47,840
He's like a caged bird, Jack.

1505
00:49:49,520 --> 00:49:51,300
You have Sam.

1506
00:49:52,300 --> 00:49:53,960
You have Allie.

1507
00:49:58,440 --> 00:50:00,090
He has no one.

1508
00:51:40,950 --> 00:51:42,230
Mummy.

1509
00:52:10,330 --> 00:52:16,710
?今晚我會保持安全?

1510
00:52:19,210 --> 00:52:25,100
?諾言我不會離開你的視線?

1511
00:52:27,660 --> 00:52:31,690
?如果你迷路?

1512
00:52:32,380 --> 00:52:35,790
?按照我的聲音?

1513
00:52:36,750 --> 00:52:41,410
?你和我，我們將是?

1514
00:52:51,240 --> 00:52:55,570
?會帶我們出去?

1515
00:52:58,340 --> 00:53:03,660
?沒有人會把我們分開?

1516
00:53:03,770 --> 00:53:05,270
The ghost.

1517
00:53:05,410 --> 00:53:08,760
?你會在這裡找到我?

1518
00:53:10,110 --> 00:53:12,960
?你和我會?

1519
00:53:57,020 --> 00:53:58,030
Jack!

1520
00:53:58,310 --> 00:53:59,640
The mirror!

1521
00:54:54,510 --> 00:54:55,650
What?

1522
00:54:56,730 --> 00:54:58,940
Sam has been to Mother's room.

1523
00:55:07,300 --> 00:55:09,420
He said he saw something in there.

1524
00:55:09,910 --> 00:55:11,810
In the wardrobe mirror.

1525
00:55:13,030 --> 00:55:15,030
He thinks he saw the ghost, Jack.

1526
00:55:17,110 --> 00:55:18,670
Well, that was just a lie we told Sam

1527
00:55:18,700 --> 00:55:20,370
so he wouldn't know the truth.

1528
00:55:22,050 --> 00:55:23,720
And the truth is we walled up a man

1529
00:55:23,820 --> 00:55:26,500
and let him die and rot over our heads.

1530
00:55:29,010 --> 00:55:30,440
Our own father.

1531
00:55:31,870 --> 00:55:33,960
He was a murderer, Jane.

1532
00:55:34,660 --> 00:55:36,210
He came here to kill us.

1533
00:55:36,410 --> 00:55:37,920
And what are we then?

1534
00:55:39,940 --> 00:55:42,320
I can still remember those screams.

1535
00:55:42,760 --> 00:55:44,520
Those first weeks.

1536
00:55:46,590 --> 00:55:48,720
It seemed like he would never die.

1537
00:55:49,210 --> 00:55:52,220
Is it so crazy to think his ghost is still up there?

1538
00:55:52,680 --> 00:55:56,100
He can't hurt us now. He's dead and gone.

1539
00:55:56,430 --> 00:55:58,150
He's not gone.

1540
00:55:59,930 --> 00:56:02,270
We need to give him a proper burial.

1541
00:56:04,280 --> 00:56:06,710
We are never going back to that place.

1542
00:56:07,330 --> 00:56:08,750
Understood?

1543
00:56:09,840 --> 00:56:10,840
Never.

1544
00:56:12,090 --> 00:56:14,020
We can't live in a tomb.

1545
00:56:37,690 --> 00:56:39,110
Oh, Allie!

1546
00:56:39,720 --> 00:56:40,790
Hello.

1547
00:56:41,390 --> 00:56:43,440
-Packing already? -Yes.

1548
00:56:43,550 --> 00:56:46,450
Uh, actually, can I see you for a moment?

1549
00:56:46,770 --> 00:56:48,600
-Of course. -Great.

1550
00:56:50,420 --> 00:56:51,510
Thank you.

1551
00:56:54,060 --> 00:56:56,840
Gosh, I'm sorry about the mess.

1552
00:56:57,010 --> 00:56:58,760
That's quite all right.

1553
00:57:05,270 --> 00:57:06,440
So?

1554
00:57:10,420 --> 00:57:12,750
There's something I...

1555
00:57:18,340 --> 00:57:19,340
Here.

1556
00:57:20,530 --> 00:57:21,870
What is this?

1557
00:57:22,380 --> 00:57:23,460
Open it.

1558
00:57:23,770 --> 00:57:25,150
Tom, I...

1559
00:57:34,650 --> 00:57:36,160
Would you be my guest?

1560
00:57:36,420 --> 00:57:38,600
There's so many places I would love to show you.

1561
00:57:38,800 --> 00:57:39,940
Tom, I...

1562
00:57:41,020 --> 00:57:43,220
I really wish you wouldn't.

1563
00:57:44,330 --> 00:57:46,250
我沖得太厲害了，不是嗎？

1564
00:57:46,380 --> 00:57:48,250
No, it's...

1565
00:57:48,910 --> 00:57:50,460
It's not that, it's just um...

1566
00:57:50,630 --> 00:57:51,840
I'm too old?

1567
00:57:51,930 --> 00:57:54,300
You know my father is 15 years older than my mother?

1568
00:57:54,460 --> 00:57:55,990
And they've been happily married

1569
00:57:56,110 --> 00:57:57,930
-for 40 years. -Tom, please. Stop.

1570
00:57:59,460 --> 00:58:02,800
I just never thought about you that way.

1571
00:58:03,150 --> 00:58:04,650
I'm sorry.

1572
00:58:15,620 --> 00:58:17,800
It's uh, about Jack, isn't it?

1573
00:58:18,040 --> 00:58:19,720
I really don't think that's any of your concern.

1574
00:58:19,830 --> 00:58:21,480
You don't know the first thing about him.

1575
00:58:21,600 --> 00:58:24,040
You have no idea...

1576
00:58:25,130 --> 00:58:27,220
what you are getting into.

1577
00:58:35,190 --> 00:58:37,030
I am only trying to protect you.

1578
00:58:37,160 --> 00:58:40,570
You know, I can get you out of this place where you don't belong.

1579
00:58:42,060 --> 00:58:43,890
You should think about that.

1580
01:00:04,590 --> 01:00:06,030
Scoundrel?

1581
01:00:08,160 --> 01:00:09,910
Where have you been?

1582
01:00:51,270 --> 01:00:54,610
Better not bite me, or I'll turn you into lunch.

1583
01:01:13,690 --> 01:01:15,570
Come on out of there.

1584
01:01:16,770 --> 01:01:18,670
Do not be afraid.

1585
01:02:26,810 --> 01:02:27,960
Thomas D. Porter.

1586
01:02:28,000 --> 01:02:29,940
Mr. Porter, This is Sam Gouldman.

1587
01:02:30,060 --> 01:02:31,460
Mr. Gouldman!

1588
01:02:32,260 --> 01:02:34,360
What a pleasure to hear from you. Actually, I was just finishing...

1589
01:02:34,430 --> 01:02:35,770
Well, we just came out of a board meeting

1590
01:02:35,890 --> 01:02:37,880
and after some heartfelt deliberations,

1591
01:02:37,970 --> 01:02:39,200
important decisions have been made

1592
01:02:39,290 --> 01:02:40,950
about the future of our firm.

1593
01:02:41,710 --> 01:02:42,770
I'm all ears.

1594
01:02:42,880 --> 01:02:44,680
The time has come for us to grow.

1595
01:02:44,760 --> 01:02:46,580
So, instead of the position we spoke about,

1596
01:02:46,660 --> 01:02:50,180
we have decided to offer you to become a partner in our firm.

1597
01:02:50,760 --> 01:02:52,140
How's that sound?

1598
01:02:52,320 --> 01:02:54,110
Well, I'm honored, sir.

1599
01:02:55,090 --> 01:02:57,550
But just to make sure I understand...

1600
01:02:57,620 --> 01:02:59,750
We're offering you the great opportunity

1601
01:02:59,840 --> 01:03:02,360
of buying ten percent of our shares.

1602
01:03:05,290 --> 01:03:06,460
Are you there?

1603
01:03:07,670 --> 01:03:10,700
And how much are we talking about roughly?

1604
01:03:10,810 --> 01:03:12,820
Well, it's a little neighborhood south of $5,000.

1605
01:03:12,920 --> 01:03:15,560
I assume this won't be a problem.

1606
01:03:16,910 --> 01:03:18,240
Right, Mr. Porter?

1607
01:03:18,550 --> 01:03:19,640
Right.

1608
01:03:20,610 --> 01:03:23,680
But the position is still secured, if I just want to...

1609
01:03:23,750 --> 01:03:25,710
I believe I've made my point clear.

1610
01:03:26,150 --> 01:03:30,890
What we need right now is a partner, not an employee.

1611
01:03:33,110 --> 01:03:34,280
Porter?

1612
01:03:36,880 --> 01:03:37,900
Porter?

1613
01:03:38,040 --> 01:03:40,050
Well, I'll have to think about it, then.

1614
01:03:40,130 --> 01:03:42,000
Well, don't sit on it too long.

1615
01:03:42,200 --> 01:03:45,110
If you're not interested, we have to move on to our next candidate.

1616
01:03:45,300 --> 01:03:47,080
I'm sure you understand it.

1617
01:03:47,560 --> 01:03:49,150
I'll call you Monday.

1618
01:03:51,510 --> 01:03:54,040
Thank you, Mr. Gouldman. Thank you.

1619
01:04:23,180 --> 01:04:25,620
No! No! No!

1620
01:04:25,850 --> 01:04:27,190
No. No.

1621
01:05:03,810 --> 01:05:05,070
Billy?

1622
01:05:14,500 --> 01:05:15,670
Jane?

1623
01:05:47,390 --> 01:05:49,620
How's your mother feeling today?

1624
01:05:51,700 --> 01:05:53,460
It seems we have a problem, Jack.

1625
01:05:55,090 --> 01:05:57,840
I can't be an accomplice to a forgery.

1626
01:05:58,710 --> 01:06:00,170
Please.

1627
01:06:00,350 --> 01:06:02,710
I'm just trying to look after my family.

1628
01:06:03,200 --> 01:06:04,560
You lied to me.

1629
01:06:04,980 --> 01:06:06,610
You tried to cheat me and in doing so,

1630
01:06:06,680 --> 01:06:08,700
you made me an accessory in your little charade.

1631
01:06:08,770 --> 01:06:11,060
So, I think it's fair you offer me some kind of compensation.

1632
01:06:11,140 --> 01:06:12,270
We have nothing!

1633
01:06:12,340 --> 01:06:15,480
You have 10,000 pounds and you will hand them over to me

1634
01:06:15,550 --> 01:06:18,950
so I can get out of this cowshit and wear real shoes again.

1635
01:06:24,250 --> 01:06:26,740
Now I assume you will discuss this with your siblings.

1636
01:06:29,720 --> 01:06:31,160
I'll come by tomorrow.

1637
01:06:46,460 --> 01:06:48,110
What are we going to do?

1638
01:06:51,290 --> 01:06:53,180
We threw that money down the chimney.

1639
01:06:53,350 --> 01:06:55,540
We have no way of getting it back now.

1640
01:06:56,510 --> 01:06:57,980
It's all over.

1641
01:08:43,760 --> 01:08:44,860
Ah!

1642
01:11:55,140 --> 01:11:57,020
Billy, give me-give me...

1643
01:11:57,120 --> 01:11:58,380
Give me that!

1644
01:11:58,540 --> 01:12:01,250
-Yeah, hold this. -Okay, okay.

1645
01:12:01,350 --> 01:12:02,310
Ah!

1646
01:12:02,360 --> 01:12:03,630
-Billy. -What? What?

1647
01:12:03,730 --> 01:12:05,010
What have you done?

1648
01:12:06,700 --> 01:12:07,780
You...

1649
01:12:07,920 --> 01:12:10,700
You didn't dare to tear down the wall.

1650
01:12:11,010 --> 01:12:13,670
So...so it found another way to the attic.

1651
01:12:13,840 --> 01:12:15,630
Someone had to try and get that money back.

1652
01:12:15,650 --> 01:12:17,840
I told you not to go in there!

1653
01:12:17,920 --> 01:12:19,450
He survived, Jack.

1654
01:12:21,030 --> 01:12:23,560
Ah! He survived, Jack.

1655
01:12:23,790 --> 01:12:25,950
He's been eating up there.

1656
01:12:26,300 --> 01:12:28,810
I saw it with my own two eyes.

1657
01:12:28,930 --> 01:12:31,440
It will kill us all. I saw it.

1658
01:12:31,510 --> 01:12:33,950
The place is covered in-- in animal bones!

1659
01:12:34,020 --> 01:12:35,470
Doves, raccoons, rats.

1660
01:12:35,560 --> 01:12:38,260
You cou--You couldn't imagine the stench in there.

1661
01:12:38,320 --> 01:12:40,400
And he's found a way to store rain water.

1662
01:12:40,440 --> 01:12:41,500
It's the rain.

1663
01:12:41,590 --> 01:12:44,170
-He's alive...again. -He's alive this whole time.

1664
01:12:45,480 --> 01:12:46,960
Get out, get out.

1665
01:12:47,120 --> 01:12:49,290
-He's got to go. -Please stop it.

1666
01:12:49,360 --> 01:12:51,080
No! Stop it?

1667
01:12:51,250 --> 01:12:54,460
Stop it? Is anybody listening to me? He's still alive!

1668
01:12:54,550 --> 01:12:56,080
And waiting to do some more damage!

1669
01:12:56,110 --> 01:12:57,270
I'm done with that son of a bitch!

1670
01:12:57,340 --> 01:12:58,370
You know I will.

1671
01:12:58,480 --> 01:13:01,180
I will go up there and I will end this, I swear to God!

1672
01:13:01,280 --> 01:13:03,780
Are you listening to me? Are you listening?

1673
01:13:03,950 --> 01:13:05,180
Jack!

1674
01:13:06,810 --> 01:13:07,810
Jack!

1675
01:13:14,710 --> 01:13:15,560
Jack.

1676
01:13:15,700 --> 01:13:17,810
Shh, calm, Jack.

1677
01:13:18,000 --> 01:13:19,250
Shh. Jack!

1678
01:13:22,620 --> 01:13:23,700
Jack!

1679
01:13:25,230 --> 01:13:27,040
We have to tell Allie.

1680
01:13:35,910 --> 01:13:37,950
She's the only one who can help him.

1681
01:13:38,530 --> 01:13:40,100
No, she'll be scared, she...

1682
01:13:40,210 --> 01:13:42,070
She won't want to see him again.

1683
01:13:42,210 --> 01:13:44,370
She loves him, Billy.

1684
01:13:44,620 --> 01:13:47,750
The only thing that matters now is saving Jack.

1685
01:13:48,490 --> 01:13:51,000
We have to tell Allie the truth.

1686
01:16:15,500 --> 01:16:16,850
Hello?

1687
01:16:29,680 --> 01:16:31,180
Anybody home?

1688
01:16:31,710 --> 01:16:33,790
I've come for my money!

1689
01:16:34,310 --> 01:16:35,570
Hello!

1690
01:17:51,370 --> 01:17:54,680
"The day we locked father up was a day like any other.

1691
01:17:55,130 --> 01:17:58,390
Nothing could have warned us that he finally found us".

1692
01:18:09,820 --> 01:18:10,880
Jack!

1693
01:18:17,020 --> 01:18:18,210
Sam!

1694
01:18:18,440 --> 01:18:19,610
Take Sam.

1695
01:18:19,900 --> 01:18:21,110
Come on, this way!

1696
01:18:21,210 --> 01:18:23,290
-Let me go with you. -No, you stay with Jane and Sam.

1697
01:18:23,360 --> 01:18:24,690
No! Jack!

1698
01:18:25,720 --> 01:18:27,190
-Jack! -Jack?

1699
01:18:27,320 --> 01:18:28,660
Should be safe here.

1700
01:18:28,740 --> 01:18:30,150
Hey, Jack!

1701
01:18:31,130 --> 01:18:32,410
-Jack! -I will deal with him.

1702
01:18:32,490 --> 01:18:34,420
Jack! No, Jack!

1703
01:18:37,440 --> 01:18:38,990
I've got it!

1704
01:18:39,560 --> 01:18:41,150
I'm right here!

1705
01:18:42,680 --> 01:18:44,940
This is between you and me!

1706
01:18:51,520 --> 01:18:54,600
Stay away from the house and I will give it back!

1707
01:19:37,600 --> 01:19:39,770
It was me and me alone.

1708
01:19:40,880 --> 01:19:42,380
I ratted you out.

1709
01:19:42,550 --> 01:19:43,920
I took your money.

1710
01:19:44,700 --> 01:19:46,470
They had nothing to do with it.

1711
01:19:47,080 --> 01:19:48,690
Take it

1712
01:19:48,880 --> 01:19:50,490
and leave us alone.

1713
01:21:48,340 --> 01:21:49,520
Jack?

1714
01:22:11,640 --> 01:22:13,260
Kill him, Billy.

1715
01:23:27,190 --> 01:23:28,550
I'm coming!

1716
01:23:28,910 --> 01:23:30,410
I'm coming!

1717
01:23:35,130 --> 01:23:36,190
Sam!

1718
01:23:36,670 --> 01:23:38,260
Sam, I'm coming!

1719
01:23:44,240 --> 01:23:45,490
Jane.

1720
01:23:47,930 --> 01:23:50,690
Jane, Billy, Sam!

1721
01:24:03,050 --> 01:24:04,210
Sam!

1722
01:24:13,200 --> 01:24:16,370
Open the door, Jack.

1723
01:24:32,840 --> 01:24:35,580
If you dare.

1724
01:24:50,290 --> 01:24:52,430
What have you done?!

1725
01:24:54,710 --> 01:24:56,970
What have you done?!

1726
01:24:57,240 --> 01:25:00,080
Jane, Billy, Sam!

1727
01:25:00,760 --> 01:25:02,520
Sam!

1728
01:25:03,010 --> 01:25:04,800
Please, Jane, Billy!

1729
01:25:26,560 --> 01:25:28,850
I'm sorry I couldn't keep you safe.

1730
01:25:30,800 --> 01:25:32,830
But I'm keeping my promise.

1731
01:26:11,510 --> 01:26:17,520
?今晚我會保持安全?

1732
01:26:20,420 --> 01:26:26,610
?諾言我不會離開你的視線?

1733
01:26:29,090 --> 01:26:32,810
?如果你迷路?

1734
01:26:33,540 --> 01:26:36,880
?按照我的聲音?

1735
01:26:38,040 --> 01:26:44,360
?你和我，我們將是一個?

1736
01:26:47,350 --> 01:26:51,560
?我們會建立一個據點?

1737
01:26:51,660 --> 01:26:53,600
?我們將在哪裡安全?

1738
01:26:53,680 --> 01:26:55,400
? Where we'll be safe ?
Billy.

1739
01:26:56,180 --> 01:26:58,780
?沒有錯的?

1740
01:26:58,920 --> 01:26:59,920
Jane.

1741
01:27:02,070 --> 01:27:03,320
Sam.

1742
01:27:04,350 --> 01:27:10,960
?如果你只是在我身邊?

